==English==
===Etymology===
Scottish - from [[numbskull]]
===Noun===
'''numptie'''
# a [[dolt]] or [[idiot]]

----
Numptie is a slang term used in the United Kingdom to refer to a fool, a dolt, or a clod, although it is normally meant in an endearing way. It was originally Scottish, but moved its way south in recent years. It can also be spelt 'Numpty'. The DLR extension to London City Airport station construction team was refered to by their manager as "a bunch of numpties" implying that he was the chief of all numpties.